**********************************************************************
MAUI Bitmap UCM Font Information demo code
**********************************************************************
What this demo does:
  - The demo prints information about UCM font in memory. Command line 
    option allows to specify font name, which has to be in the memory.

**********************************************************************
System requirements:
  - A working MAUI environment is assumed.
 
**********************************************************************
Directories: 
  - Source code 
      $MWOS/SRC/MAUI/DEMOS/SFONT
        
**********************************************************************
To make this demo:
  - From the source file directory type:
      % os9make
 
**********************************************************************
Operation:
 
  - This demo has several command line options. Run it with -h or -? 
    option to find out what options are supported. "-f" option specifies 
    font name . If no font name is specified, "default.fnt" font is used.

      $ sfont -f=<my_font.fnt>

**********************************************************************
 
